rComments: He is not the clearest speaker, but he is a very enthusiastic teacher who keeps the topics interesting. Essays questions are not the most well-written ones, but I think they are so broad on purpose so everyone can adopt them to his/her background.

Kalyviotis approaches his teaching as if the students are also accomplished engineers. This style makes him sometimes hard to track in lecture, especially when he answers specific students' questions. He assumes that all the students have the same understanding e.g. in mathematics with the student asked the question.
Not boring guy with empirical examples and original ideas

The course was very interesting and covered infrastructure and xities theory (the first in MEngCEM). Grading was based on a project presentation and an essay. The project was ok, but the essay was very difficult.
Prof Kalyviotis is a nice guy, easy-going and generous in grading. He makes eye contact with students etc, but he talks a lot! None in the class got less than B+, I think the most of us got A-.

He brings a positive energy and enthusiasm to the class. He gestures to slides, the blackboard and use his hands to explain concepts. He moves quite quickly through concepts. He waits 3.5 seconds before answering the question himself, and it is better to wait around 7 seconds at least for students to formulate responses.
